The '''second inauguration of James Madison''' as the [[List of Presidents of the United States|fourth]] [[President of the United States]] was held on Thursday, March 4, 1813, in the House chamber of the U.S. Capitol.{{dubious|date=January 2009}}. The [[United States presidential inauguration|inauguration]] marked the commencement of the second four-year term of [[James Madison]] as President and the only term (which lasted approximately one and a half years) of [[Elbridge Gerry]] as [[Vice President of the United States|Vice President]]. [[John Marshall]], Chief Justice, administered the [[Oath of office of the President of the United States|oath of office]] to Madison.<ref>{{cite web |title=President James Madison, 1813 |url=http://inaugural.senate.gov/history/chronology/jmadison1813.cfm |publisher=Joint Congressional Committee on Inaugural Ceremonies |accessdate=2009-01-23}}</ref>

